          "japanese": "これはほんです。",
          "reading": "Kore wa hon desu.",
          "meaning": "This is a book."
        }
      ],
      "notes": "です (desu) is the polite copula, similar to 'is/am/are' in English. は (wa) marks the topic of the sentence.",
      "difficulty": 1
    },
